1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:17,460
=Episode 12=
(This story is entirely fictional.)

17
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,760
Since this is a poetry contest,

18
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:22,280
I shall also compose a poem.

19
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:29,080
Green hills can't hide
the summer clouds in flight.

20
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:33,200
At night, a traveler's boat
docks by the river's side.

21
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,600
A lady fair passed
through this town of misty rain.

22
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:40,120
In this fleeting world, we sing,
drunk on life's refrain.

23
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,080
Sir, your poem

24
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:44,480
tells us you hail from faraway lands

25
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,920
and subtly mentions a humble maiden

26
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,080
passing through Feng City.

27
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,440
The ending, with its drunkenness,

28
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,520
perfectly matches the theme.

29
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,000
It is indeed a cut

30
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,000
above Mr. Lu's poem.

31
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,120
It should be deemed
the best of the evening.

32
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,600
Way to go, Yunzhuo.

33
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,000
- Brilliant poem!
- What a verse!

34
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,400
- So impressive!
- Wonderful!

35
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,120
Wonderful!

36
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,920
Have we still not dug up anything

37
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,280
on this owner of Xianquan Tavern?

38
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,200
My lord,

39
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,280
about that...

40
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,200
We're still investigating.

41
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:21,680
Useless wretch!

42
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,280
Can't even handle a simple task?

43
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,320
What do I even keep you for?

44
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,760
(You? Keep me?)

45
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,760
(What does the Marquis House have now?)

46
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,920
(Not a darn coin.)

47
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,880
(I pay for every person
I send on errands)

48
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,280
(out of my own pocket.)

49
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,880
(Have you ever
chipped in a single coin?)

50
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,400
Anyone else?

51
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,160
Care to share a poem?

52
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,880
If there are no more,

53
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,560
then Mr. Zhao takes the crown.

54
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,720
I declare

55
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,520
the winner
of today's poetry gathering is...

56
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:17,560
Not so fast!

57
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,120
I have newly composed a poem today

58
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,880
and would like
to ask Miss Xue for her thoughts.

59
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:28,680
So Mr. Chen

60
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,560
is ready to step into the ring.

61
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,880
What a shame.

62
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,680
If Mr. Chen hadn't stepped up,

63
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:36,120
that fellow just now
would've had it in the bag.

64
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,200
Once the Top Scholar makes a move,

65
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,120
that other guy hasn't got a prayer.

66
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,440
That prick

67
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,880
hasn't even passed
the palace examination yet.

68
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:42,800
He's only aced the written test,

69
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:45,360
and he already swans around
calling himself the Top Scholar.

70
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,520
If he ruins this for me,

71
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,120
I'll make sure he never

72
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:49,960
becomes a Top Scholar.

73
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,880
Drunk, I lie on a beauty's lap.

74
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:56,120
Sober,
the scent of fine wine brings me back.

75
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:59,080
To live a life like this,

76
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,880
who would still crave
the emperor's golden robes?

77
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:02,720
Bravo!

78
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,400
What a peerless masterpiece!

79
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,320
Oh my, when Mr. Chen does it,

80
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,760
it's truly in a league of its own!

81
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:12,160
Bravo! What a peerless poem!

82
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,200
Mr. Lu is still watching.

83
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,280
Now that he has composed a poem,

84
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:19,480
like it or not,

85
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,080
we have to show him respect.

86
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:25,120
Oh my, worthy of the Top Scholar!

87
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,520
They're all big shots
we can't afford to cross.

88
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,680
But...

89
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,720
No "buts."

90
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,960
Zhao Yunzhuo

91
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,760
is merely the owner of Xianquan Tavern.

92
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,280
Aside from deep pockets,

93
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,320
he's no one.

94
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,680
Yunzhuo, think up a few more poems now.

95
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,600
Composing poetry isn't something
you just pull out of thin air.

96
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,080
Hurry, think!

97
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,000
Poetry needs inspiration,
which is essential.

98
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,320
What would you know?

99
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,120
Mr. Wang, you do it.

100
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,480
Your Highness,

101
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,680
I'm not up to it.

102
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,360
I'm utterly unlettered.

103
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,320
Everyone in the capital knows it.

104
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,520
Are we just going to sit here and watch

105
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:01,880
the Marquis House's men take the crown

106
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,080
and walk away with that thing?

107
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:03,640
Your Majesty,

108
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,560
I can recognize a few characters,

109
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:06,520
but

110
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,760
I truly cannot compose poetry.

111
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,240
Besides, Chen Hongyun

112
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,600
hasn't taken the palace exam yet,

113
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,080
but he possesses real talent.

114
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,400
Is there truly no one

115
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,760
who can outshine him?

116
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:22,880
(Right.)

117
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:25,280
(How could I
have forgotten about that guy?)

118
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:39,280
Chen, your vision is truly grand,

119
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,520
and your words are like fine brocade.

120
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,160
Truly worthy of

121
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:43,160
our dynasty's Top Scholar title.

122
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,320
Once the Top Scholar acts,

123
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,160
he truly stands above the rest,

124
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,400
unrivaled and unmatched.

125
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,280
Truly impressive.

126
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,680
Hmm?

127
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,080
So,

128
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,720
is my poem not up to scratch?

129
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,800
It certainly is.

130
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,480
My lord, you and the Top Scholar
can be hailed

131
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:02,720
as the twin jewels
of Daqian's poetry scene.

132
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,480
That's right.

133
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,720
My lord,
your poetic talent is unparalleled.

134
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,800
Were you not uninterested
in poetic composition,

135
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,880
you'd surely be
shining like the moon above,

136
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,760
illuminating
the literary world of Daqian.

137
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:13,920
Hear, hear.

138
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,080
Li Yunhe, quick, do something.

139
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:20,880
Bring Chen Hongyun down a peg

140
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,120
and dampen their arrogance.

141
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,400
Don't be ridiculous.

142
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,920
He's the Top Scholar.

143
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:25,960
Besides,

144
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,080
don't you see all those people

145
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,400
sucking up to him?

146
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,880
If you're willing to step in,

147
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,360
I'll give you 500 taels of silver.

148
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,520
Miss Zhao,

149
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,680
you can't seriously be unaware

150
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,760
of the weight
the title "Top Scholar" carries.

151
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,520
He's personally chosen by His Majesty.

152
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,320
His brilliance
overshadows an entire generation.

153
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:48,680
(He didn't say yes,)

154
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,880
(but he didn't say no.)

155
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,040
(Could it be this guy)

156
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,360
(thinks I'm lowballing him?)

157
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,360
Anyone else care to compose a poem?

158
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,680
Then I declare...

159
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,120
Li Yunhe,

160
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,080
as long as you can beat Chen Hongyun,

161
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:15,120
I'll give you half of Xianquan Tavern.

162
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,680
Today's champion is

163
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,760
the new Top Scholar...

164
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,680
Hold it right there!

165
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,880
Half the restaurant. That's settled,

166
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,280
plus 500 taels of silver.

167
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,000
Ms. Sun,

168
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,800
I haven't even started yet.

169
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,640
How can you just call it a day

170
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,080
and announce it's over?

171
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,800
Mr. Li,

172
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,920
are you planning to duke it out

173
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,560
with the new Top Scholar
for today's crown?

174
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,280
Li Yunhe,

175
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:55,080
composing poetry
isn't like a duel of verses.

176
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,600
You might want
to think twice before you speak,

177
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:00,080
or you'll just end up
embarrassing yourself.

178
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:04,160
Just an illiterate country bumpkin

179
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:07,200
who lucked his way
into beating me just once.

180
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,480
And now you dare bark at my friend Chen?

181
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,400
Do you even get

182
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,600
what "Top Scholar" actually means?

183
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,880
You really have a death wish, don't you?

184
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:17,480
Haha, Li Yunhe,

185
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,480
you really think you can beat me

186
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,760
at my own game?

187
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,080
Let me give you a tip.

188
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,320
Don't be so cocky, young man.

189
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,400
If you're not cocky,

190
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,480
can you even call yourself young?

191
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,680
The sheer insolence!

192
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,000
He doesn't know his place at all.

193
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,600
He's just a live-in son-in-law.

194
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:34,160
What right does he have to compete

195
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,360
with the Top Scholar?

196
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,880
Have a reality check already.

197
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,880
Do you even know what you're doing?

198
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,760
Who do you think

199
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,480
you are

200
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,160
to bet against the Top Scholar?

201
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,240
You can't be stupid enough

202
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:46,320
to think poetry
is a piece of cake, right?

203
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,680
Mr. Lu,

204
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,280
I must have forgotten.

205
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,640
Who was it the other day

206
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,600
who matched verses with me
outside the Zhou Manor

207
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,000
and worked himself up
into a fainting spell?

208
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,680
(Daqian's Poet Laureate)
(Don't tell me you're stumped again?)

209
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,880
It's alright.

210
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,520
I'm working hard to make money now,

211
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,680
so I can

212
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:13,160
buy out your contract
from the Zhou family sooner.

213
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,080
Li Yunhe,

214
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,600
what little game are you playing now?

215
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,320
I think

216
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,480
he's probably scared stiff

217
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,520
by Mr. Chen
and your sheer talent, my lord.

218
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,360
He's just talking big,

219
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,160
then he's going to slip away.

220
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,080
Idiot!

221
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,320
You think everyone is
as brainless as you?

222
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,680
My lord, you can count on it.

223
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,480
Since he's dared to stir up trouble,

224
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,680
I'll make sure his name is mud

225
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,680
and nail him
to the whipping post for good.

226
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,200
What's he up to now?

227
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,720
Spill it.

228
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,760
How much

229
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,440
did you pay him this time?

230
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,160
Half of Xianquan Tavern,

231
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,200
plus 500 taels of silver.

232
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,800
Half the tavern?

233
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,800
He already owns a 20 percent stake.

234
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,960
You're giving him another 50 percent?

235
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,800
We'll end up the outsiders!

236
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,480
The thing Xue Bingxiu is holding

237
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,160
could rock
the very foundations of Daqian.

238
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,080
And you're griping
about money at a time like this?

239
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:04,000
It's not the money I'm griping about.

240
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:07,080
He's got some clever tricks,

241
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,160
but when it comes to real poetry,

242
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,720
how can he possibly beat Chen Hongyun?

243
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,520
This is just

244
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,880
throwing money down the drain.

245
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,680
(Grandfather's death
has far-reaching consequences.)

246
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,000
(This secret edict I carry)

247
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,960
(must be passed
to the right hands eventually.)

248
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:24,480
(It's better
to let Li Yunhe take a swing)

249
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,600
(and stir up the hornet's nest.)

250
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,400
Mr. Li,

251
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,800
since you have the talent,

252
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,480
simply step up to the stage

253
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,800
and let it shine.

254
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:34,360
Yu,

255
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:35,880
go sit back down

256
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,200
in a moment

257
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,920
and keep a little distance from me

258
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,200
because I'm about

259
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,280
to unleash some serious swagger.

260
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,480
Hey, you.

261
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,640
You're starting on the booze

262
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,880
at a time like this?

263
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,600
Don't tell me you're getting cold feet.

264
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,480
Let me clue you in,

265
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,720
it's way too late.

266
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,240
Even if you're
so scared you piss your pants,

267
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,520
it won't do you any good now.

268
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,360
Isn't it just

269
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:08,000
a poem about wine?

270
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,080
Fine, I'll whip one up for you.

271
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,280
Lend me your ears.

272
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:19,680
Behold the Yellow River,
descending from heaven,

273
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:25,280
surging to the sea, never back.

274
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,920
The Yellow River descending from heaven?

275
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,680
So the river at your place

276
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,400
just falls out of the sky?

277
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,280
You call that poetry?

278
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:41,880
Brilliant!

279
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,080
What an opening.

280
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,680
Behold the Yellow River,
descending from heaven,

281
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,760
surging to the sea, never back.

282
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:48,680
Such mighty vigor,

283
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:49,880
so natural and seamless.

284
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,400
A peerless line
that will echo through the ages.

285
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,600
Behold,

286
00:11:56,080 --> 00:12:00,520
in gilded halls, bright mirrors
mourn our fleeting raven hair.

287
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:05,920
At dawn like black silk threads,
by dusk a field of snow.

288
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:10,760
When life serves up joy,
drink deep and savor every drop.

289
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:15,600
Never let your golden cup
sit idly beneath the moon.

290
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,720
Heaven gave me talents,
destined for a grand design.

291
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:24,520
A fortune squandered?
It will all come back in time.

292
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,080
So, bring in the wine.

293
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,960
Let the cups keep coming.

294
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,560
I'll sing you a song.

295
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:40,160
Please, bend your ears and listen well.

296
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,080
What a poem!

297
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:47,080
- Marvellous!
- What a talent!

298
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:49,240
- Amazing, absolutely incredible!
- Just wonderful!

299
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:52,160
- Simply divine!
- Exquisite!

300
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:53,600
Truly a masterpiece!

301
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,720
A timeless poem!

302
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,400
Exquisite! Simply exquisite!

303
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,000
He's a once-in-a-century genius,

304
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,320
a talent sent from above!

305
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,320
(That man's)

306
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,280
(got my heart racing
all over the place.)

307
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,360
(If I actually had him castrated,)

308
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,480
(it would be a real pity.)

309
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,160
Your Majesty,

310
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:09,680
with a poem like this from Mr. Li,

311
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,120
the business you're after
is as good as done.

312
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:14,520
It's just Xianquan Tavern

313
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,560
might soon have a new owner, I'm afraid.

314
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,760
You don't see it.

315
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,960
A drinking poem of this magnitude...

316
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,520
Not just half a tavern,

317
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,680
even ten, a hundred like it,

318
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,760
could never measure up.

319
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:29,200
I have an eye for talent like no other.

320
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,920
Heaven gave me talents,
destined for a grand design.

321
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,280
A fortune squandered?
It will all come back in time.

322
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,200
How...

323
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,680
How can there be

324
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:43,880
such fine poetry in this world?

325
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:46,520
(Over five thousand years of history,)

326
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,960
(Top Scholars come and go
like fish in a river.)

327
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,680
(But the great poet Li Bai's
"Bringing in the Wine")

328
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,360
(is the absolute summit of wine poetry.)

329
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:55,560
(What have you got)

330
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,360
(to even put up a fight?)

331
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,280
Impossible!

332
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,960
This is absolutely impossible.

333
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:02,800
Li Yunhe,

334
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,800
come clean now!

335
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,080
Where did you plagiarize this from?

336
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,520
Impossible is

337
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,880
all you can say.

338
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,080
Lu Qifeng.

339
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,560
Is that the only line you know,

340
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,480
so you keep babbling it?

341
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,680
It's just a drinking poem.

342
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,440
I'll whip up another one.

343
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,760
No big deal.

344
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:20,480
Listen up, and listen good.

345
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:29,320
By the river, I saw a friend off
into the night.

346
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:34,760
Maple leaves and reed flowers
rustled in the autumn's bite.

347
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:39,000
I raised my cup to drink,
but there was no music in the air.

348
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:45,080
Drunk, but not in joy,
we parted in a bleak despair.

349
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:50,600
As we parted, the vast river
drowned in the moon's pale gleam.

350
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:56,920
Who among the seated guests
shed the most tears tonight?

351
00:14:57,200 --> 00:15:00,680
Our Top Scholar, so frightened
he soaked his trousers in sheer fright.

352
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:02,560
Li Yunhe!

353
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:03,520
Li Yunhe, you...

354
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,280
Impossible! Absolutely impossible!

355
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,800
These two poems...

356
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:14,480
Any single one
would grant a man immortality.

357
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,920
To write one is a miracle.

358
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:18,280
How could you, of all people,

359
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,480
rattle them off like this?

360
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:20,480
How absurd.

361
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,720
You mean these poems
weren't written by Li Yunhe?

362
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,360
What, were they written by you?

363
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:25,920
Shut it!

364
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,400
You're just a vulgar merchant.

365
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,400
How could you possibly write two poems

366
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:29,520
of such vastly different styles?

367
00:15:29,520 --> 00:15:30,920
They're clearly plagiarized!

368
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,360
My lord.

369
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,480
There's no need
to argue with them, Zhuo.

370
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,640
Since Mr. Chen

371
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,720
doesn't believe I wrote them,

372
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,680
I'll just compose another one,
nice and easy.

373
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:48,560
(Heh.)

374
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,800
(Back when I was in elementary school,)

375
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,480
(I could recite
hundreds of these from memory.)

376
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,760
Listen up.

377
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:57,680
Ugh.

378
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:58,680
What's going on here?

379
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,720
Mr. Chen!

380
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:33,860
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

381
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:37,220
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

382
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:40,460
♪Who took the March rain♪

383
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:44,060
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

384
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:47,220
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

385
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:50,580
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

386
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:57,380
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

387
00:16:57,420 --> 00:17:00,860
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

388
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,940
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

389
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,380
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

390
00:17:06,380 --> 00:17:10,580
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

391
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:13,940
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

392
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:17,220
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

393
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:20,660
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

394
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:27,340
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

395
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:57,140
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

396
00:17:57,380 --> 00:18:00,540
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

397
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:03,860
♪Who took the March rain♪

398
00:18:04,060 --> 00:18:07,380
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

399
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:10,660
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

400
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:14,460
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

401
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:17,780
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

402
00:18:17,780 --> 00:18:20,740
♪As seasons change♪

403
00:18:20,740 --> 00:18:24,380
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

404
00:18:24,380 --> 00:18:27,220
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

405
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,860
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

406
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:33,940
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

407
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:37,260
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

408
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:40,980
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

409
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:44,500
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

410
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:47,380
♪Only for you♪

411
00:18:47,380 --> 00:18:50,980
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

412
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:53,860
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

413
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:56,540
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

414
00:18:56,540 --> 00:19:00,620
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

415
00:19:00,620 --> 00:19:03,940
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

416
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:07,340
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

417
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:13,860
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

418
00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:19,060
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

419
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:24,860
♪Your wedding gown♪
